  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">,&nbsp;then peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces </span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> and&nbsp;<strong>peeled&nbsp;garlic</strong>&nbsp;to a pot of plenty of&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return them to the pot</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Roll each piece of<strong> pork tenderloin</strong> in 2 rashers of<strong> smoked streaky bacon</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> wrapped pork</strong>&nbsp;to the pan and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until browned&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: turn the pork very gently so the bacon doesn't fall off&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the<strong> pork&nbsp;</strong>to an oiled baking tray (reserve the pan for step 7!)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>honey</strong> over the<strong> pork </strong>&nbsp;and put in the oven for 7-9<span class=\"text-highlight\"> min</span> or until cooked through&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once done, remove from the oven and leave to rest until serving</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rip the leaves off the<strong> spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up &amp; slice into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> sliced spring greens</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>\r\n<p>Once tender, drain and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mash until smooth</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pour away most of the&nbsp;<strong>oil</strong> from the pork tenderloin&nbsp;pan, leaving around 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;in the pan</p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>clotted cream</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 1 min, whisking&nbsp;until fully combined &ndash; this is your&nbsp;<strong>wholegrain mustard sauce&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1198.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>pork tenderloin</strong> pieces in half</p>\r\n<p>Serve the<strong>&nbsp;pork tenderloin</strong> over the<strong> wholegrain mustard sauce</strong> with the<strong> mashed potato</strong> and<strong> spring greens</strong> to the side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
